{"type":"message","id":"cc3f946c","parentId":"188670a7","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:03:22.700Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-09 19:03 EST] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: # TASK: Fix agent-watchdog for Real Observability\n\n## CONTEXT\nThe `agent-watchdog` skill is currently classified as PARTIAL because it has recovery logic but NO REAL MONITORING. There's no evidence of actual observability or monitoring activity.\n\n## PROBLEM ANALYSIS\nCurrent state (defective):\n- Recovery code exists but never triggered\n- No monitoring directory (`~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`)\n- No real session/task monitoring\n- No observable monitoring logs or artifacts\n- \"Monitoring\" exists only in documentation\n\nRequired state (functional):\n- Real monitoring of agent sessions/tasks\n- Observable monitoring logs/artifacts\n- Real session registration and tracking\n- Actual stall detection in real workflows\n- Recovery actions triggered when appropriate\n\n## YOUR MISSION\nConvert `agent-watchdog` from simulated monitoring to REAL observability.\n\n## SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS\n\n### 1. Create Real Monitoring Infrastructure\n- Create directory: `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`\n- Implement session registration system\n- Create monitoring logs with real data\n- Track actual runtime metrics\n\n### 2. Implement Real Session Monitoring\n- Monitor real OpenClaw agent sessions\n- Track session duration, activity, state\n- Detect stalls based on real metrics (not simulated)\n- Create observable monitoring artifacts\n\n### 3. Enable Real Recovery Triggers\n- Recovery logic should trigger based on REAL monitoring data\n- Not based on simulated or placeholder data\n- Recovery actions should have observable effects\n\n### 4. Integration with Real Workflows\n- Monitor actual sub-agent executions\n- Track real task progress\n- Detect real stalls in distributed execution\n- Emit real incidents to error-learning-loop\n\n## FILES TO MODIFY/CREATE\n1. `scripts/watchdog_monitor.py` - NEW: Real session monitoring\n2. `scripts/watchdog_recovery.py` - ENHANCE: Trigger based on real monitoring\n3. `scripts/watchdog_integration.py` - NEW: Integration with OpenClaw sessions\n4. `config/watchdog_config.yaml` - Configuration for monitoring\n5. `SKILL.md` - Update to reflect real capabilities\n\n## DELIVERABLES\n1. **Real monitoring infrastructure** (directory, logs, registration)\n2. **Updated recovery logic** triggered by real monitoring\n3. **Test evidence** showing:\n   - Real session monitoring (not simulated)\n   - Observable monitoring logs/artifacts\n   - Real stall detection (not simulated)\n   - Recovery triggered based on real data\n4. **Integration evidence** with error-learning-loop\n5. **Handoff report** with outcome and incidents\n\n## EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS (Anti-simulation)\n- NO placeholder monitoring directories\n- NO fake session IDs or monitoring data\n- NO simulated stall detection\n- REAL monitoring logs with actual session data\n- REAL recovery triggers based on actual metrics\n- REAL incident emission when appropriate\n\n## TEST SCENARIOS TO PROVE\n1. **Monitoring Reality Test**: Show real session being monitored\n2. **Stall Detection Test**: Create real stall scenario, show detection\n3. **Recovery Trigger Test**: Show recovery triggered by real monitoring data\n4. **Integration Test**: Show incidents emitted to error-learning-loop\n\n## TIMELINE\n- Start: Immediate\n- Complete: Within 30 minutes\n- Report: Concise handoff with evidence\n\n## SUCCESS CRITERIA\n`agent-watchdog` moves from PARTIAL to FUNCTIONAL in certification matrix when:\n1. Real monitoring infrastructure exists and works\n2. Real sessions are being monitored (not simulated)\n3. Real stall detection occurs (not simulated)\n4. Recovery triggers based on real monitoring data\n5. Evidence shows real observability (logs, artifacts, metrics)\n\nFocus on making monitoring REAL, not just documenting it."}],"timestamp":1773101002697}}
