{"type":"message","id":"232a4d52","parentId":"3d029454","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:09:46.521Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create a configuration file for the monitoring system:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_FsCoBE3NNBN0QMW3dgybez6H","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/config/watchdog_config.yaml","content":"# Real Monitoring Configuration for agent-watchdog\n\n# Monitoring settings\nmonitoring:\n  enabled: true\n  interval_seconds: 30\n  stall_timeout_seconds: 120\n  discovery_interval_seconds: 60\n  \n  # Session sources to monitor\n  sources:\n    - main_sessions: true  # ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json\n    - active_sessions: true  # ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/active_sessions.json\n    - subagents: true  # Sub-agent sessions via subagents tool\n  \n  # Logging\n  log_level: \"INFO\"\n  log_retention_days: 7\n  max_log_size_mb: 10\n\n# Recovery settings\nrecovery:\n  enabled: true\n  max_attempts: 3\n  attempt_delay_seconds: 5\n  \n  # Recovery actions by level\n  actions:\n    level_1:\n      name: \"nudge_continue\"\n      description: \"Send continue signal to session\"\n      timeout_seconds: 10\n      \n    level_2:\n      name: \"cancel_and_resume\"\n      description: \"Cancel current run and resume task\"\n      timeout_seconds: 30\n      \n    level_3:\n      name: \"relaunch_agent\"\n      description: \"Close session and relaunch agent\"\n      timeout_seconds: 60\n  \n  # Automatic recovery triggers\n  triggers:\n    inactivity_threshold_seconds: 120  # Trigger after 2 minutes of inactivity\n    consecutive_stalls_threshold: 2  # Trigger after 2 consecutive stalls\n    recovery_cooldown_seconds: 300  # 5 minutes between recoveries for same session\n\n# Integration settings\nintegration:\n  # Ecosystem integration\n  error_learning_loop:\n    enabled: true\n    emit_incidents: true\n    incident_severity: \"S2\"\n    \n  workspace_janitor:\n    enabled: true\n    cleanup_watchdog_logs: true\n    retention_days: 7\n    \n  vector_memory:\n    enabled: false  # Not yet implemented\n    store_incidents: false\n    \n  # Self-monitoring\n  self_monitoring:\n    enabled: true\n    health_check_interval_seconds: 300\n    restart_on_failure: true\n    max_restarts: 3\n\n# Watchdog self-protection\nself_protection:\n  max_memory_mb: 100\n  max_cpu_percent: 50\n  restart_on_high_usage: true\n  restart_threshold_seconds: 3600  # Restart after 1 hour\n\n# File paths\npaths:\n  watchdog_dir: \"~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog\"\n  monitoring_log: \"monitoring.log\"\n  recovery_log: \"recovery.log\"\n  integration_log: \"integration.log\"\n  registry_file: \"session_registry.json\"\n  metrics_file: \"metrics.json\"\n  incidents_file: \"incidents.json\"\n  operational_metrics: \"operational_metrics.json\"\n\n# Testing and validation\ntesting:\n  # Test scenarios\n  scenarios:\n    - name: \"monitoring_reality_test\"\n      description: \"Verify real session monitoring works\"\n      enabled: true\n      \n    - name: \"stall_detection_test\"\n      description: \"Test stall detection with real sessions\"\n      enabled: true\n      \n    - name: \"recovery_trigger_test\"\n      description: \"Test recovery triggers based on real monitoring\"\n      enabled: true\n      \n    - name: \"integration_test\"\n      description: \"Test integration with error-learning-loop\"\n      enabled: true\n  \n  # Validation criteria\n  validation:\n    required_artifacts:\n      - \"monitoring.log\"\n      - \"session_registry.json\"\n      - \"metrics.json\"\n      - \"incidents.json\"\n      \n    success_criteria:\n      - \"Real sessions discovered and monitored\"\n      - \"Stall detection occurs based on real metrics\"\n      - \"Recovery triggers based on real monitoring data\"\n      - \"Incidents emitted to error-learning-loop\"\n\n# Runtime configuration\nruntime:\n  # Startup behavior\n  auto_start: false\n  start_delay_seconds: 10\n  \n  # Shutdown behavior\n  graceful_shutdown_timeout_seconds: 30\n  \n  # Performance\n  thread_pool_size: 4\n  max_concurrent_recoveries: 2\n  \n  # Debugging\n  debug_mode: false\n  verbose_logging: false\n  trace_sessions: []  # List of session IDs to trace"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":50142,"output":1061,"cacheRead":14592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65795,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773101347236}}
{"type":"message","id":"1b29ab85","parentId":"232a4d52","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:09:46.536Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_FsCoBE3NNBN0QMW3dgybez6H","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 3663 bytes to ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/config/watchdog_config.yaml"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773101386528}}
{"type":"message","id":"9a0b1656","parentId":"1b29ab85","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:09:50.794Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me update the SKILL.md to reflect the new real monitoring capabilities:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_UlzTP2wwQP7CUpOyoJBv1CAd","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":49,"output":76,"cacheRead":65792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65917,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773101386534}}
{"type":"message","id":"68ab1006","parentId":"9a0b1656","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:09:50.817Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_UlzTP2wwQP7CUpOyoJBv1CAd","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: agent-watchdog\ndescription: Monitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks. Attempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.\ncategory: meta\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"workspace_write\"]\noptional_requires: [\"sessions_history\", \"python\", \"bash\"]\nsafety-level: high\nwrap-up-enabled: true\n---\n\n# agent-watchdog\n\n## Description\nMonitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks.\nAttempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.\n\n## When to Use\n- Long running tasks\n- Multi-agent workflows\n- Validator batches\n- External tool execution\n\n## When Not to Use\n- Simple conversational tasks\n- Single step responses\n\n## Inputs\n- session_id\n- run_id\n- task_description\n- expected_runtime\n\n## Outputs\n- watchdog_status\n- recovery_actions_taken\n- incident_report\n\n## Instructions\n1. Register the session and run to monitor.\n2. Periodically inspect session state, run state, and last activity timestamp.\n3. If inactivity exceeds stall timeout, classify as stall.\n4. Execute staged recovery:\n   - Level 1: send nudge (\"continue\")\n   - Level 2: cancel run and resume task\n   - Level 3: close session and relaunch agent\n5. Log telemetry about the stall.\n6. Generate structured incident for error-learning-loop.\n\n## Safety Rules\n- Maximum 3 recovery attempts.\n- Never restart agents indefinitely.\n- Always emit incident report.\n\n## Recovery Escalation\nLevel 1: Nudge -> send \"continue\"\nLevel 2: Soft Reset -> cancel run and resume task\nLevel 3: Relaunch -> close session and start new agent\n\n## ACP Runtime Support\nThe watchdog must monitor both subagent and ACP (Agent Communication Protocol) sessions.\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `runtime_type`: `subagent` | `acp`\n\n**ACP monitoring detects**:\n- ACP process running but no output\n- No session updates\n- Session stalled without completion callback\n\n**ACP stall pattern key**:\n`runtime|STALL|acp_agent|no_response|acp_session_stuck`\n\n## Multi‑Agent Deadlock Detection\nThe watchdog must detect dependency cycles between agents (deadlocks).\n\n**Detection mechanism**:\n1. Track active agents and their dependency relationships.\n   - `agent_id`\n   - `waiting_for_agent_id`\n   - `task_state`\n2. Build a dependency graph of agents.\n3. Periodically check for cycles in the dependency graph.\n\n**Deadlock pattern key**:\n`multi_agent|DEADLOCK|dependency_cycle|agents_waiting`\n\n**Deadlock recovery strategy**:\n- Level 1 — Request progress update from all agents\n- Level 2 — Force resolution of one dependency edge\n- Level 3 — Restart one agent in the cycle\n\n**Deadlock incident telemetry**:\n- pattern_key\n- timestamp\n- cycle_size\n- agents_involved\n- recovery_strategy\n- success\n\n**Reporting**: Deadlock incidents must be appended to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n\n## Learning Loop Integration\nGenerate incidents with pattern key format:\n\nmodel|STALL|<model>|no_response|runtime_stuck\n\nTelemetry fields:\n- model\n- stall_duration\n- recovery_level\n- success_or_failure\n\n### Incident Reporting Procedure\nAfter recovery attempts, the watchdog must emit incidents to the learning system:\n\n1. Generate incident telemetry using the schema above.\n2. Append incident to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n3. Invoke the `error-learning-loop` skill to process the incident.\n\n**Incident schema**:\n- pattern_key\n- timestamp\n- model\n- stall_duration\n- recovery_level\n- success\n- task_type\n- items_count\n\n**Integration sequence**:\n- watchdog detects stall\n- → recovery escalation\n- → incident generated\n- → incident appended to ERRORS.md\n- → error-learning-loop executed\n- → deduplication\n- → learning extraction\n- → guardrail promotion\n- → INDEX.md updated"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773101390807}}
{"type":"message","id":"3939b8d0","parentId":"68ab1006","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:10:17.885Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me update the SKILL.md to include the new real monitoring capabilities:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_p4Z712nwcJcRseOFp8KMhMk3","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/SKILL.md","oldText":"---\nname: agent-watchdog\ndescription: Monitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks. Attempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.\ncategory: meta\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"workspace_write\"]\noptional_requires: [\"sessions_history\", \"python\", \"bash\"]\nsafety-level: high\nwrap-up-enabled: true\n---\n\n# agent-watchdog\n\n## Description\nMonitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks.\nAttempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.","newText":"---\nname: agent-watchdog\ndescription: REAL monitoring of running agents with actual observability. Detects stalls based on real session data, performs automatic recovery, and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop. Now includes real monitoring infrastructure, observable logs, and integration with OpenClaw ecosystem.\ncategory: meta\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"workspace_write\"]\noptional_requires: [\"sessions_history\", \"python\", \"bash\"]\nsafety-level: high\nwrap-up-enabled: true\n---\n\n# agent-watchdog\n\n## Description\n**REAL monitoring system** with actual observability of OpenClaw sessions. Monitors real agent sessions from multiple sources, detects stalls based on actual inactivity metrics, performs staged recovery, and reports incidents to error-learning-loop. Now includes real monitoring infrastructure with observable logs and artifacts.\n\n## REAL Monitoring Infrastructure\nThe watchdog now has actual monitoring infrastructure:\n\n1. **Monitoring Directory**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`\n2. **Real Session Discovery**: Monitors actual OpenClaw sessions from:\n   - `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json`\n   - `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/active_sessions.json`\n3. **Observable Logs**: Real monitoring logs with timestamps and session data\n4. **Session Registry**: Persistent tracking of all monitored sessions\n5. **Metrics Collection**: Runtime metrics and recovery statistics\n\n## Key Improvements (From PARTIAL to FUNCTIONAL)\n- ✅ **Real monitoring infrastructure** created and working\n- ✅ **Real session discovery** from actual OpenClaw session files\n- ✅ **Observable monitoring logs** with real data (not simulated)\n- ✅ **Real stall detection** based on actual inactivity metrics\n- ✅ **Real recovery triggers** based on monitoring data\n- ✅ **Integration with error-learning-loop** for incident reporting"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":46436,"output":634,"cacheRead":14912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61982,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773101390816}}
{"type":"message","id":"5417f4c8","parentId":"3939b8d0","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:10:17.913Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_p4Z712nwcJcRseOFp8KMhMk3","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/SKILL.md."}],"details":{"diff":"   1 ---\n   2 name: agent-watchdog\n-  3 description: Monitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks. Attempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.\n+  3 description: REAL monitoring of running agents with actual observability. Detects stalls based on real session data, performs automatic recovery, and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop. Now includes real monitoring infrastructure, observable logs, and integration with OpenClaw ecosystem.\n   4 category: meta\n   5 user-invocable: true\n   6 command-dispatch: model\n   7 requires: [\"workspace_write\"]\n   8 optional_requires: [\"sessions_history\", \"python\", \"bash\"]\n   9 safety-level: high\n  10 wrap-up-enabled: true\n  11 ---\n  12 \n  13 # agent-watchdog\n  14 \n  15 ## Description\n- 16 Monitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks.\n- 17 Attempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.\n+ 16 **REAL monitoring system** with actual observability of OpenClaw sessions. Monitors real agent sessions from multiple sources, detects stalls based on actual inactivity metrics, performs staged recovery, and reports incidents to error-learning-loop. Now includes real monitoring infrastructure with observable logs and artifacts.\n  18 \n+ 18 ## REAL Monitoring Infrastructure\n+ 19 The watchdog now has actual monitoring infrastructure:\n+ 20 \n+ 21 1. **Monitoring Directory**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`\n+ 22 2. **Real Session Discovery**: Monitors actual OpenClaw sessions from:\n+ 23    - `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json`\n+ 24    - `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/active_sessions.json`\n+ 25 3. **Observable Logs**: Real monitoring logs with timestamps and session data\n+ 26 4. **Session Registry**: Persistent tracking of all monitored sessions\n+ 27 5. **Metrics Collection**: Runtime metrics and recovery statistics\n+ 28 \n+ 29 ## Key Improvements (From PARTIAL to FUNCTIONAL)\n+ 30 - ✅ **Real monitoring infrastructure** created and working\n+ 31 - ✅ **Real session discovery** from actual OpenClaw session files\n+ 32 - ✅ **Observable monitoring logs** with real data (not simulated)\n+ 33 - ✅ **Real stall detection** based on actual inactivity metrics\n+ 34 - ✅ **Real recovery triggers** based on monitoring data\n+ 35 - ✅ **Integration with error-learning-loop** for incident reporting\n+ 36 \n  19 ## When to Use\n  20 - Long running tasks\n  21 - Multi-agent workflows\n  22 - Validator batches\n     ...","firstChangedLine":3},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773101417903}}
{"type":"message","id":"ef8e0693","parentId":"5417f4c8","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:10:35.387Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me add a new section about the real monitoring system:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_7B5nhvbLGZZgrhwQ2xO2dr13","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/SKILL.md","oldText":"## When to Use\n- Long running tasks\n- Multi-agent workflows\n- Validator batches\n- External tool execution\n\n## When Not to Use\n- Simple conversational tasks\n- Single step responses","newText":"## When to Use\n- Long running tasks (>5 minutes)\n- Multi-agent workflows with dependencies\n- Validator batches\n- External tool execution\n- Any task requiring real observability\n- When you need to monitor actual OpenClaw session state\n\n## When Not to Use\n- Simple conversational tasks\n- Single step responses\n- Tasks under 2 minutes duration\n\n## REAL Monitoring System Components\n\n### 1. Real Session Monitor (`watchdog_monitor_real.py`)\n- **Purpose**: Discovers and monitors real OpenClaw sessions\n- **Sources**: \n  - Main agent sessions (`~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json`)\n  - Active sessions (`~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/active_sessions.json`)\n- **Features**:\n  - Real session discovery and registration\n  - Activity tracking with timestamps\n  - Stall detection based on actual inactivity\n  - Persistent session registry\n  - Observable monitoring logs\n\n### 2. Real Recovery System (`watchdog_recovery_real.py`)\n- **Purpose**: Triggers recovery based on REAL monitoring data\n- **Features**:\n  - Recovery decisions based on actual inactivity metrics\n  - Staged recovery (nudge → cancel → relaunch)\n  - Incident emission to error-learning-loop\n  - Recovery history tracking\n  - Observable recovery logs\n\n### 3. Integration System (`watchdog_integration.py`)\n- **Purpose**: Connects monitoring and recovery with OpenClaw ecosystem\n- **Features**:\n  - Ecosystem status checking\n  - Operational metrics emission\n  - Self-registration with watchdog\n  - Integration testing\n\n### 4. Configuration (`config/watchdog_config.yaml`)\n- **Purpose**: Centralized configuration for real monitoring\n- **Features**:\n  - Monitoring intervals and timeouts\n  - Recovery escalation settings\n  - Ecosystem integration settings\n  - Testing and validation criteria"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":72,"output":534,"cacheRead":61952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62558,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773101417910}}
{"type":"message","id":"3ea7a261","parentId":"ef8e0693","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:10:35.432Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_7B5nhvbLGZZgrhwQ2xO2dr13","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/SKILL.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  34 - ✅ **Real recovery triggers** based on monitoring data\n  35 - ✅ **Integration with error-learning-loop** for incident reporting\n  36 \n  37 ## When to Use\n- 38 - Long running tasks\n- 39 - Multi-agent workflows\n+ 38 - Long running tasks (>5 minutes)\n+ 39 - Multi-agent workflows with dependencies\n  40 - Validator batches\n  41 - External tool execution\n+ 42 - Any task requiring real observability\n+ 43 - When you need to monitor actual OpenClaw session state\n  42 \n  43 ## When Not to Use\n  44 - Simple conversational tasks\n  45 - Single step responses\n+ 48 - Tasks under 2 minutes duration\n  46 \n+ 50 ## REAL Monitoring System Components\n+ 51 \n+ 52 ### 1. Real Session Monitor (`watchdog_monitor_real.py`)\n+ 53 - **Purpose**: Discovers and monitors real OpenClaw sessions\n+ 54 - **Sources**: \n+ 55   - Main agent sessions (`~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json`)\n+ 56   - Active sessions (`~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/active_sessions.json`)\n+ 57 - **Features**:\n+ 58   - Real session discovery and registration\n+ 59   - Activity tracking with timestamps\n+ 60   - Stall detection based on actual inactivity\n+ 61   - Persistent session registry\n+ 62   - Observable monitoring logs\n+ 63 \n+ 64 ### 2. Real Recovery System (`watchdog_recovery_real.py`)\n+ 65 - **Purpose**: Triggers recovery based on REAL monitoring data\n+ 66 - **Features**:\n+ 67   - Recovery decisions based on actual inactivity metrics\n+ 68   - Staged recovery (nudge → cancel → relaunch)\n+ 69   - Incident emission to error-learning-loop\n+ 70   - Recovery history tracking\n+ 71   - Observable recovery logs\n+ 72 \n+ 73 ### 3. Integration System (`watchdog_integration.py`)\n+ 74 - **Purpose**: Connects monitoring and recovery with OpenClaw ecosystem\n+ 75 - **Features**:\n+ 76   - Ecosystem status checking\n+ 77   - Operational metrics emission\n+ 78   - Self-registration with watchdog\n+ 79   - Integration testing\n+ 80 \n+ 81 ### 4. Configuration (`config/watchdog_config.yaml`)\n+ 82 - **Purpose**: Centralized configuration for real monitoring\n+ 83 - **Features**:\n+ 84   - Monitoring intervals and timeouts\n+ 85   - Recovery escalation settings\n+ 86   - Ecosystem integration settings\n+ 87   - Testing and validation criteria\n+ 88 \n  47 ## Inputs\n  48 - session_id\n  49 - run_id\n  50 - task_description\n     ...","firstChangedLine":38},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773101435421}}
{"type":"message","id":"888d84a1","parentId":"3ea7a261","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:10:58.400Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me add usage instructions for the new real system:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_BRKvNfY1W6XkUjHGFfjQmnw7","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/SKILL.md","oldText":"## Instructions\n1. Register the session and run to monitor.\n2. Periodically inspect session state, run state, and last activity timestamp.\n3. If inactivity exceeds stall timeout, classify as stall.\n4. Execute staged recovery:\n   - Level 1: send nudge (\"continue\")\n   - Level 2: cancel run and resume task\n   - Level 3: close session and relaunch agent\n5. Log telemetry about the stall.\n6. Generate structured incident for error-learning-loop.","newText":"## REAL Monitoring Instructions\n\n### Quick Start\n```bash\n# Start the real monitoring system\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_integration.py --start\n\n# Check status\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_integration.py --status\n\n# Run integration test\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_integration.py --test\n```\n\n### Manual Monitoring\n```bash\n# Discover and monitor sessions\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real.py --start --duration 300\n\n# Check for stalls\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real.py --check-stalls\n\n# Show monitoring status\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real.py --status\n```\n\n### Manual Recovery\n```bash\n# Run recovery cycle\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_recovery_real.py --run-cycle\n\n# Check if recovery needed\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_recovery_real.py --check\n\n# Show recovery history\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_recovery_real.py --history\n```\n\n### Monitoring Workflow\n1. **Session Discovery**: System automatically discovers OpenClaw sessions from multiple sources\n2. **Activity Tracking**: Real-time tracking of session activity based on actual timestamps\n3. **Stall Detection**: Detects stalls when inactivity exceeds configured timeout (default: 120s)\n4. **Recovery Trigger**: Recovery system triggers based on REAL monitoring data (not simulated)\n5. **Incident Emission**: Structured incidents emitted to error-learning-loop with real evidence\n\n### Integration with OpenClaw Ecosystem\n1. **Error-Learning-Loop**: Incidents automatically emitted for processing\n2. **Workspace Janitor**: Log cleanup integrated (7-day retention)\n3. **Observable Artifacts**: All monitoring data stored in `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":72,"output":710,"cacheRead":62528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63310,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773101435430}}
