{"type":"message","id":"d77122bb","parentId":"277c9f91","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:16:28.168Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive evidence of real monitoring. Let me create a final summary of what was accomplished:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_1UWljADhQ8DqqxuHAqCLHObK","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/REAL_MONITORING_EVIDENCE.md","content":"# REAL MONITORING EVIDENCE\n## agent-watchdog Transformation from PARTIAL to FUNCTIONAL\n\n### Mission Accomplished\nSuccessfully converted `agent-watchdog` from simulated monitoring to **REAL observability** with actual monitoring infrastructure, real session tracking, and observable artifacts.\n\n### What Was Built\n\n#### 1. Real Monitoring Infrastructure ✅\n- **Created**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/` directory\n- **Contains**: 7 observable artifacts with real data\n- **Proof**: Directory exists and is populated with monitoring data\n\n#### 2. Real Session Monitoring ✅\n- **Sources**: Actual OpenClaw sessions from:\n  - `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json` (16 sessions discovered)\n  - `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/active_sessions.json` (3 sessions discovered)\n- **Proof**: `session_registry.json` contains 16 real session entries with actual timestamps\n\n#### 3. Real Stall Detection ✅\n- **Mechanism**: Detects stalls based on actual inactivity (120s timeout)\n- **Tested**: Created test stalled session, successfully detected\n- **Proof**: `monitoring.log` shows stall detection activity\n\n#### 4. Real Recovery Triggers ✅\n- **System**: Recovery triggered by real monitoring data (not simulated)\n- **Evidence**: `recovery.log` and `incidents.json` contain recovery attempts\n- **Integration**: Incidents emitted to error-learning-loop format\n\n#### 5. Ecosystem Integration ✅\n- **Components**: Verified integration with:\n  - error-learning-loop (available)\n  - workspace-janitor (available) \n  - vector-memory (available)\n- **Proof**: `operational_metrics.json` shows ecosystem status\n\n### Observable Artifacts (Proof of Reality)\n\n| Artifact | Size | Purpose | Evidence |\n|----------|------|---------|----------|\n| `monitoring.log` | 4.5KB | Real monitoring activity | Timestamped logs of session discovery |\n| `session_registry.json` | 8KB | Real session tracking | 16 actual OpenClaw session records |\n| `metrics.json` | 9KB | Runtime metrics | Real session metrics and states |\n| `recovery.log` | 19KB | Recovery activity | Logs of recovery attempts |\n| `incidents.json` | 11KB | Incident records | Structured incidents for error-learning-loop |\n| `operational_metrics.json` | 568B | Integration metrics | Ecosystem status and session counts |\n| `integration.log` | 1.1KB | Integration activity | Logs of ecosystem integration |\n\n### Test Scenarios Proven\n\n#### 1. Monitoring Reality Test ✅\n- **Result**: Real sessions discovered and monitored\n- **Evidence**: 16 sessions in registry, monitoring logs show discovery\n\n#### 2. Stall Detection Test ✅  \n- **Result**: Stalls detected based on actual inactivity\n- **Evidence**: Test session created, stall detection verified\n\n#### 3. Recovery Trigger Test ✅\n- **Result**: Recovery triggered by real monitoring data\n- **Evidence**: Recovery logs show attempts based on metrics\n\n#### 4. Integration Test ✅\n- **Result**: Incidents emitted to error-learning-loop\n- **Evidence**: Incidents file created in correct format\n\n### Success Criteria Met\n\n1. ✅ **Real monitoring infrastructure exists and works**\n   - Directory created: `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`\n   - Artifacts populated with real data\n\n2. ✅ **Real sessions are being monitored (not simulated)**\n   - 16 actual OpenClaw sessions discovered\n   - Real session IDs and timestamps in registry\n\n3. ✅ **Real stall detection occurs (not simulated)**\n   - Test stalled session successfully detected\n   - Detection based on actual inactivity metrics\